      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Boom colt HOLLYWOOD STRIP (3) stretched his unbeaten run to eight when overcoming the outside barrier for a huge win in the NSW Derby at Menangle last start. He looks the real deal and can push forward to dictate from the good draw. Hard to go past him. SOHO PARK AVENUE (7) was nearly 14m behind HOLLYWOOD STRIP in the Derby but there was merit in his other two starts this time in, finishing fourth to the same rival first up at Listed level along with a placing in his Derby heat. Yet to miss a place at this distance so can fill a top-three spot again. YOU GOTTA BELIEVE (6) started a hot favourite when runner-up at Wagga last time but that was his first start for 11 months so it should have improved him and he is proven at this circuit and distance, winning a Gold Crown heat last season. MAXO MIGHTY (4) was down the track in a Derby heat last start but did come from this barrier for a fresh win at Menangle three back.",
